 "https://api.github.com/users/rustbot/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rustbot/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rustbot/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rustbot/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rustbot/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2019-12-13T13:35:46Z", "updated_at": "2019-12-20T14:30:48Z", "closed_at": "2019-12-20T14:30:48Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Over in https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/65951, @estebank and I were discussing that we could improve the error message in cases like:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/3964a55ba59bb6c3d4badcbddc49f6929ef76862/src/test/ui/async-await/unresolved_type_param.rs#L8-L14\r\n\r\nPresently, we say:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/master/src/test/ui/async-await/unresolved_type_param.stderr#L1-L5\r\n\r\nbut this `T` we reference comes from the definition of `bar`:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/3964a55ba59bb6c3d4badcbddc49f6929ef76862/src/test/ui/async-await/unresolved_type_param.rs#L6\r\n\r\nit'd be nice if we said \"cannot infer value for type parameter `T` declared on the fn `bar`\".\r\n\r\nI believe that name comes from the [`TypeParameterDefinition`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/nightly-rustc/rustc/infer/type_variable/enum.TypeVariableOriginKind.html#variant.TypeParameterDefinition) information that we track as part of a type variable's origin:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/3964a55ba59bb6c3d4badcbddc49f6929ef76862/src/librustc/infer/error_reporting/need_type_info.rs#L159-L161\r\n\r\nSo we could do this by modifying that variant to track the `DefId` of the type parameter and then looking at the parent to derive the context.\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_START -->\nThis issue has been assigned to @ohadrav